<br>
/salute to all Meatsheilds like my self.<br>
<br>
I am 46 seasons, Barbarian Warrior, and my brain is like blue screened. <br>
<br>
I think I want a wurmslayer...hunted with a guildmate of mine, and that thing wails! But...at this point, I tend to be puller/ tank for the groups I hunt with. I know in a couple of seasons, things will change, then keeping aggro as a MT will be more important, but for now, I  tend to be the main damage giver as well. I dont seem to get to hunt with mages/wiz's too much. So in this scenario, the Wurmslayer seems appropriate. Question, I have read many forums and posts all over many various boards, and am confused.<br>
<br>
Question..if the wurmy is Primary only, then would I have my Lammy in secondary..or another high damage , slower delay in secondary. Does the secondary weapon only need to be equal or just less ( DLY) or should it be as fast as possible.<br>
<br>
I'm currently swinging Lammy (9/19)in primary, Jagged blade of mourning in off(13/25), but last night broke out the old centi warhammer (15/32) for secondary, and it seemed to kill the giants faster in Vel with the slower/more damage weapon. I realize this scenario is opposite If I get the wurmy as it's primary..but just lookin for feedback.<br>
<br>
So..is the wurmy worth it? I do have  SCHW for hasteing the slowness of it. and about the secondary...as fast or less, or defiantly faster?<br>
<br>
