<br>
Simply plug in the numbers. Use the highest value weapon in your primary and the second highest value in your off hand.<br>
<br>
( (damage * 2) + damage bonus ) / ( delay / 10 )<br>
<br>
Looking at the wapons you have available to you...<br>
<br>
At 46, damage bonus is 7...<br>
Wurm = 14.25<br>
Jagged = 13.20<br>
Lammy = 13.16<br>
Centi WH = 11.56<br>
<br>
At 49, damage bonus is 8...<br>
Wurm = 14.50<br>
Lammy = 13.67<br>
Jagged = 13.60<br>
Centi WH = 11.87<br>
<br>
And just hypothetically, at 58, damage bonus is 11...<br>
Lammy = 15.26<br>
Wurm = 15.25<br>
Jagged = 14.80<br>
Centi WH = 12.81<br>
<br>
This formula is for maximizing your damage only and does not take into account procs or wanting to hold aggro as an MT.<br>
<br>
As you can see, while the Wurm does put out good damage, the faster weapons start to quickly catch up to it's output as you progress through the 50s. And as a side note, it is really hard to hold aggro with past 50 or 51.<br>
<br>
In my personal opinion, hold on to your Lammy/Jagged Blade combo and save your coin. They are good weapons and can last you into your mid 50s. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
