<br>
Rubbish, have you ever parsed wepon damage?<br>
<br>
The only good thing about lammy+jagged is they make nice taunting wepons, the spread of hits is constant enough to keep you high on the list.......however even with a 27/42 two handed wepon, i could outtaunt that combo easy without casting spells, just pure melee and taunt.<br>
<br>
Seriously, go parse some damage on the 2 handed, and test for taunt... personally i never had any problems with taunting and 2 handed wepons, in most circumstances 2 handed &gt; dual wield in taunt, depends on gear and situation though.<br>
<br>
Take a 40 damage wepon, thats going to hit for 200+<br>
<br>
Buffed and if i concentrate on offence as an shadowknight, with a 42 damage wepon i can hit 220 unbuffed average high, and around 240 ish with some different buff selections.<br>
<br>
If i hit for 240/240 on one swing....... how is a warrior going to get taunt off me? they dont, they have to wait till i miss 8 times in a row, more like 20-30 times, until they can catch up, and every double hit i get it makes it harder.<br>
<br>
Take for instance mobs that aoe stun like some dragons, i hit 200/200 on first swing, warrior will never be able to get taunt back ever, as every time i come out of stun i would get 220/100 and warrior would be hitting way way less than that, then aoe stun landed.<br>
<br>
For big fights, you should use a 2 handed wepon for first swing, then swap - only way to beep up agro fast enough.<br>
<br>
Braellar<br>
